dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root c Ashwin b Mohammed Shami 113 (108b 10x4 3x6 133m) SR: 104.62

dismissalComment.html: goes across his stumps, scoops... but straight to short fine leg! Root goes for 113, a rattling good innings though England would have loved him to still be there at the end. Tried to be a bit too cute, the ball was a half-volley on off stump, instead of hitting down the ground he ramped it softly to the fielder on the edge of the ring

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler run out (Dhoni) 49 (40b 5x4 2x6 45m) SR: 122.5

dismissalComment.html: tries to reverse sweep and hit on the pads, big appeal, not given... but Buttler has wandered blindly off down the pitch and is run out by a mile! The impact was probably outside off stump, the ball only bobbled a yard or two wide of Dhoni but for reasons unknown Buttler decided there was a run to be taken. Dhoni nonchalantly reached to his right, picked up the ball and broke the stumps, Buttler shot down short of his fifty

dismissalComment.html: spun out, Cook top-edges a sweep straight up in the air! England's captain didn't heed the warning from the previous over, falls short of a half-century, that's the end of a miserable series for him. At least he was trying to be positive I suppose

dismissalText.commentary: Alex Hales c Rahane b Yadav 4 (9b 0x4 0x6 14m) SR: 44.44

dismissalComment.html: this has gone straight up in the air! Umesh gets a wicket immediately! You have to question the choice of the shot there.. it was not that short but Hales wanted to pull it over midwicket, only gets cramped for space and gets a big top-edge that is gobbled up at midwicket

dismissalText.commentary: Moeen Ali c Yadav b Kumar 9 (8b 2x4 0x6 11m) SR: 112.5

dismissalComment.html: oh no Moeen! What was the point of that shot! This is a wide length ball and Moeen throws his at at it like this is the last over of an innings.. he gets a big outside edge that is swallowed by Umesh at third man..What a waste that was

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja b Finn 87 (68b 9x4 2x6 87m) SR: 127.94

dismissalComment.html: bowled him, Jadeja chops on! A strange dismissal, in keeping with the last few overs, really... Jadeja got well outside leg, the ball was fired in full and he effectively defended the ball on to his stumps. Finn bellows in celebration, a second wicket for him wraps up a 41-run win for England

commentPostTextItems.html: 6.25pm: India have sprayed the bubbly around, celebrating with the series trophy. And in the melee, Virat Kohli has gone tumbling over the sponsor's hoarding - been a tough tour for him, no doubt. There's still a T20 left to play, with the winner taking the spoils after a 3-1 and a 1-3 in the Tests and ODIs; join us again on Sunday for the last number of the set, the final curtain on England's international summer. From Dev and myself, thanks for your comments, cheerio for now.

6.10pm: Right, Nasser is on the dais, time for the presentations... Joe Root is named Man of the Match: "Great to play at your home ground, the crowd have been exceptional and good to get a win. Tough to start with, then the conditions got a bit easier, good to take it on. I tried not to think too much and play on instinct. We knew it would spin, spoke to the guys who'd played county one-day cricket here, nice to see what we worked on go well, that's a positive. I enjoy playing with Jos and the way he played kickstarted the back end of our innings."

Suresh Raina is named Man of the Series: "It was good, I've worked hard on my batting, watching the Tests on TV. We got the belief in the one-dayers. I worked hard on the mental side and my fitness. Looking to bat positive, the circumstances and who you are batting with. The World Cup is around the corner, we need to stay positive. We've worked hard on our game and this group has won us the series. The fielding creates a positive environment in the circle and that has been important."

England captain Alastair Cook: "That's a far better performance, and that's what we can play like. It's frustrating not to play like that before. Joe showed what he can do and that's what we've been missing in our batting. We've got a lot of 20s and 30s, the first time a guy goes on and gets a hundred we have a better chance. You saw how hard it was to chase down 300. We just played better, we didn't want to lose 4-0. It's frustrating... In the first game, we were 50 for 0 off nine overs, but we needed to build more big partnerships. They were two down by the first ten and we were ahead of the game. This is the first time we've got a massive chunk of one-day cricket and we can focus on that. We've got a bit of a break, then Sri Lanka, batting against spin, then the tri-series in Australia. So preparation will be perfect and hopefully we can improve and show it at the World Cup."

India captain MS Dhoni: "Should be fine, bit of precaution with some icing [on his hand]. We gave away too many wickets, quite a lot of soft dismissals, and because of that we were not able to chase the runs. Shikhar, Ambati, myself, we should not have lost those wickets, in the last ten overs we can get those runs but we lost soft dismissals. I think 300 was a par score on that pitch. It may have been [a case of foot off the gas], it's something that's happened in the past, in four-, five-game series. We need to improve our slog, the last ten overs with the bowling, Shami has done a good job but other fast bowlers need to step up. We don't want to concede so many we can't chase them down. The most difficult thing [is keeping everyone fit], this England tour has been 77 days, then we go to Australia before the World Cup, so it will be important to stay fresh."

6pm: England pop their cherry in the final ODI of the series, then, meaning India have to make do with a 3-1 win, a reverse of the Test result. You sense India were a little less fussed about this one, a slightly slack display with both ball and bat - Jadeja belting an extra 40-odd runs for the last wicket on his own altered the margin of what was a pretty comfortable victory. Not sure it changes much about either team's chances at the World Cup but Joe Root and the Yorkshire crowd can at least remember this one fondly. It also ends a run of five consecutive ODI defeats for England, so some small comfort for Alastair Cook too.

commentPreTextItems.html: Reminds me of that Misbah innings in the World Cup semi-final, this. Match lost then he starts swinging like a barn door

commentTextItems.html: steps away to leg, Finn follows him, Jadeja weaves his hips out of the way and takes the wide
more clean striking, short and slightly wide, clubbed over point by the free-swinging Jaddu
length ball outside off, steps away and flays the ball wide of mid-off for another boundary

commentPreTextItems.html: Steven Finn returns for the penultimate over. Jadeja is just playing for his average now...

commentTextItems.html: short ball, on leg stump, pulls through square and turns down the single again
full on leg stump, swats one down to fine leg - new career best in ODIs for Jadeja

commentPostTextItems.html: "When ants fly, most of them drop dead, those that survive start their own colony." On this evidence, Jadeja can start afresh after this, Sukhbir R

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: picks the slower ball this time, carts it over midwicket, bounces in front of the rope and beats deep square leg running around
steps away and slogs a slower ball to midwicket, again turns down a single
banged in short, pulled down to fine leg - dot ball. Curious approach, this
short ball, rising up around the ears, pulled down to fine leg and there's again no run

commentPreTextItems.html: James Anderson returns, the required rate has risen still, despite that over

commentTextItems.html: full and slightly wide, Jadeja makes room and cracks a drive to mid-off, could have been one but Sir Jaddu wants more
short ball, outside leg, paddled behind square to the man on the fence, who fields it this time

commentPostTextItems.html: "Jadeja is trying to ape Dhoni! He has been as successful as an ant trying to fly!" Well, he's going okay at the minute, Sahil... And anyway, can't some ants fly?

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: another boundary, third in the over! This is a terrific shot, backed away and laced a drive through extra cover, another punch to the solar plexus
full length, clubbed away between deep midwicket and long-on... They get back for two
good yorker in response, right up in the blockhole
another four, full toss swung towards fine leg, where the ball bobbles slightly and throws Woakes a dummy, skips past him to the boundary
full and wide, Jadeja spears a drive through the covers, gets it into a gap and that will be four more
turns one more square on the leg side

commentPostTextItems.html: I don't want to spoil anyone's dinner... but remember James Faulkner at Brisbane?

commentTextItems.html: short ball, pulled through wide long-on and they come racing back for two

goes big again... in fact, goes ENORMOUS! Gets right under the attempted yorker, leans back like an Olympic hammer thrower, sends this into orbit out towards wide long-on. Brilliant hitting, though might have been useful a few overs ago

headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Alastair Cook c Dhoni b Raina 46 (64b 6x4 0x6 77m) SR: 71.87

dismissalComment.html: spun out, Cook top-edges a sweep straight up in the air! England's captain didn't heed the warning from the previous over, falls short of a half-century, that's the end of a miserable series for him. At least he was trying to be positive I suppose

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Eoin Morgan st Dhoni b Ashwin 14 (34b 1x4 0x6 20m) SR: 41.17

dismissalComment.html: tries to use the feet, there's spin again... stumped him! Like a fly caught in the web, Morgan has been struggling, fighting, now he's been put out of his misery. Good work from Dhoni, finished the job with Morgan a yard out of his crease, forlornly trying to get his foot back

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Jos Buttler run out (Dhoni) 49 (40b 5x4 2x6 45m) SR: 122.5

dismissalComment.html: tries to reverse sweep and hit on the pads, big appeal, not given... but Buttler has wandered blindly off down the pitch and is run out by a mile! The impact was probably outside off stump, the ball only bobbled a yard or two wide of Dhoni but for reasons unknown Buttler decided there was a run to be taken. Dhoni nonchalantly reached to his right, picked up the ball and broke the stumps, Buttler shot down short of his fifty

dismissalText.commentary: Joe Root c Ashwin b Mohammed Shami 113 (108b 10x4 3x6 133m) SR: 104.62

dismissalComment.html: goes across his stumps, scoops... but straight to short fine leg! Root goes for 113, a rattling good innings though England would have loved him to still be there at the end. Tried to be a bit too cute, the ball was a half-volley on off stump, instead of hitting down the ground he ramped it softly to the fielder on the edge of the ring

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Woakes b Mohammed Shami 9 (9b 2x4 0x6 9m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: bulls eye! Another yorker and this time bang on middle stump, Woakes wasn't worried about his toes, having stepped away, but was summarily cleaned up

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane c Morgan b Anderson 0 (3b 0x4 0x6 2m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: that's the start England were after! Rahane pushes at this wider length delivery and slices it straight to point. A touch of laziness in that shot.

dismissalText.commentary: Shikhar Dhawan b Ali 31 (44b 4x4 1x6 54m) SR: 70.45

dismissalComment.html: slog and thwack! But it's the kind that makes the bowler happy.. Dhawan tries to repeat the shot and Moeen smartly slows it down. As the bat swings across, it just meets thin air. The ball then walks past and strikes the middle

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Cook b Anderson 13 (21b 2x4 0x6 25m) SR: 61.9

dismissalComment.html: we have seen it a few times this summer! Eighth time this summer, Anderson gets Kohli. This is short of length just outside off, Kohli pokes at that from the crease and gets a thick outside edge. Cook at first slip dives low to his right and completes a regulation catch

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Alastair Cook player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ambati Rayudu c Cook b Stokes 53 (65b 3x4 2x6 89m) SR: 81.53

dismissalComment.html: ooh la la! Rayudu can only hit it as far as mid-on! He was looking for a big hit over midwicket but this one came quicker of the surface and hurried Rayudu on the pull. That he was charging down the pitch didn't help either. It only gets as far as mid-on where Cook back-pedals and takes a simple catch

dismissalText.commentary: Suresh Raina c Buttler b Ali 18 (23b 2x4 0x6 27m) SR: 78.26

dismissalComment.html: faster, bounces a touch - takes the top edge, Raina goes! Not sure if this was a long hop or a pseudo-bouncer from Moeen, it was definitely dragged down, Raina went back to cut and the ball Jack-in-the-boxed through to the keeper, via a chunk of bat

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: MS Dhoni player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni c Stokes b Finn 29 (42b 1x4 1x6 63m) SR: 69.04

dismissalComment.html: he gives it away! Short and wide, should have either been left as it would have been a wide, or should have been slapped over the infield... Dhoni is disappointed though as he toe-ends this straight into the hands of the cover fielder. He had to reach out for that and couldn't control it.. Good low catch by the fielder, but Finn knows this was a gift for him..

dismissalText.commentary: Ravindra Jadeja b Finn 87 (68b 9x4 2x6 87m) SR: 127.94

dismissalComment.html: bowled him, Jadeja chops on! A strange dismissal, in keeping with the last few overs, really... Jadeja got well outside leg, the ball was fired in full and he effectively defended the ball on to his stumps. Finn bellows in celebration, a second wicket for him wraps up a 41-run win for England

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Ravichandran Ashwin c Finn b Stokes 16 (19b 1x4 0x6 28m) SR: 84.21

dismissalComment.html: slower ball, bit of a legcutter, top-edged straight up... Ashwin is outtathere! Stokes is all smiles (and freckles), duped the batsman there, woolly heave across the line and Finn it was again taking the catch in the covers, falling flat on his back in relief

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Bhuvneshwar Kumar run out (Finn/Stokes) 1 (3b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 33.33

dismissalComment.html: England hitting their marks here, Jadeja pushes off the pads and wants two again... but Bhuvnesh is struggling as the throw comes in from mid-on. Stokes was standing some way from the stumps, had to take the throw and then reach to break the wicket; Bhuvnesh is short, by a cat's whisker, India eight down

headshotImage.caption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ben Stokes player page headshot cutout, 2021
